components.value: Zhib - You are done Rabban, at the end you were nothing more than a coward.
Omozra - Your water has no value, you are a dishonor to your people.
A grain of sand in the great dune.
Rabban - You did this to me… To the great Glossu Rabban
Harkonnen, the beast! You should be kneeling down before me
like the insects that you are. Nothing more than ants...
Omozra - You are right, we should save the great Rabban. What were we thinking...
Zhib - Give him the antidote, quick!
Omozra throws Rabban his bait pouch, filled to the brim
with the harkonnen that died in the underground.
Rabban - I knew you would understand, but still, you will be executed for your sins...
Rabban’s smile disappeared after he opened the pouch
and saw the teeth of a worm appearing right under him.
He tried to move but the poison was already too deep in his system.
The last words from Rabban were the most hellish scream
a man could hear in the whole galaxy. leaving only behind
his head as a trophy after the worm had ended him.
